Description: Shoulder and neck fragment of North Ionian pottery oinochoe. Inside of neck glazed, reserved below; exterior: neck glazed, tiers of double-outlined tongues on shoulder, compass-drawn with faded added colour at centre.
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the National Museum of Scotland. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GH.065)
CVA Edinburgh / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum National Museums of Scotland Edinburgh (p.9, pl. 7,8) (listed as Corinthian)
